Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.13,0:00:10.54,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Weiss...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.31,0:00:14.11,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Oh, I fell asleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.11,0:00:15.74,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,Shh.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.01,0:00:21.84,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,Cream and five sugars. \NJust how you like it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.62,0:00:24.79,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,Here. Coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.20,0:00:33.21,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Thanks, Weiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.80,0:00:38.29,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,You've caused so much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.29,0:00:41.97,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,I thought I could trust you \Nto help me protect what's precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.04,0:00:47.98,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I thought I was doing the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.98,0:00:50.98,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Weiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.27,0:00:55.74,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I just felt bad for them \Nbeing locked up like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.81,0:01:00.40,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,I understand exactly how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.13,0:01:06.02,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,That's why you can get away \Nwith things that I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.76,0:01:07.82,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.82,0:01:11.27,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,You can move through the castle \Nwalls and the city freely.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.65,0:01:16.13,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,Actually, I understand how Yang feels, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.95,0:01:22.85,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,When I see you, it makes me \Nwant to set them free, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.85,0:01:25.69,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,Not exactly to spoil them, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.38,0:01:30.77,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Didn't you hate me \Nbecause I was so embarrassing?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.20,0:01:35.40,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,Well, I do find your simplistic \Nand reckless nature questionable.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.60,0:01:38.71,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,But I know I can count on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.71,0:01:40.88,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Oh? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.88,0:01:41.91,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.84,0:01:47.16,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,Also, I've never met anyone \Nelse lonelier than myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.58,0:01:51.17,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,You're lonely, Weiss?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.17,0:01:53.67,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,But I... oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.15,0:02:04.15,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. You are, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.39,0:02:11.95,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,In order to not to lose those precious \Nto you, lock them away carefully,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.55,0:02:14.07,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,and put them to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.89,0:02:19.65,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Oh! Speaking of precious things, \Nmy Crescent Rose.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.65,0:02:21.95,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,The barrel is actually on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.95,0:02:24.01,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,You got that wrong, Weiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.97,0:02:30.23,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,No, Ruby. Everything has its reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.95,0:02:32.44,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.44,0:02:37.46,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,After all, it hides in the shadow \Nof the person you're facing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.46,0:02:39.42,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Weiss, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.24,0:02:43.82,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,I, too, must go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.83,0:02:47.08,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Aren't we sleeping here together?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.90,0:02:50.48,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I guess you don't like \Nthe bunk bed after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.75,0:02:54.32,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,I always, always wanted one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.13,0:02:58.36,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,But this is your dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.11,0:03:02.73,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,I have to return to my own place of sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.00,0:03:05.16,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,Don't you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.92,0:03:10.83,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Yeah, I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.48,0:03:16.38,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,Good night, Ruby.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.36,0:03:23.77,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Good night, Weiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.31,0:05:07.03,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Hey! Ruby!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.03,0:05:09.37,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Hey! What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.17,0:05:12.04,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Ruby! Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.51,0:05:14.73,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Seriously? Ruby!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.27,0:05:35.85,main,Ozpin,0,0,0,,Is the situation serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.30,0:05:39.44,main,Shion,0,0,0,,Ruby has been trapped \Nby a dream inside the dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.10,0:05:43.21,main,Shion,0,0,0,,The Nightmare must have \Nsnuck inside her heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.89,0:05:48.04,main,Shion,0,0,0,,My Semblance is being obstructed \Nand can't help her escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.92,0:05:50.13,main,Pyrrha,0,0,0,,Jaune...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.13,0:05:51.41,main,Nora,0,0,0,,What? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.41,0:05:52.83,main,Ren,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.50,0:05:55.28,main,Pyrrha,0,0,0,,His Aura is getting stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.83,0:06:01.20,main,Negative Weisses,0,0,0,,Go for it, Jaune! One, two! One, two!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.20,0:06:06.01,main,Negative Weisses,0,0,0,,Go for it, Jaune! One, two! One, two!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.49,0:06:05.09,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,A little more...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.36,0:06:15.50,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Weiss!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.73,0:06:18.64,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Ow. Ow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.64,0:06:19.98,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Is this the train?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.22,0:06:26.05,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Are you awake? Thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.68,0:06:28.24,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,My last coin...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.48,0:06:41.20,main,Shion,0,0,0,,It is not clear how, but she \Nappears to be out of danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.49,0:06:46.08,main,Shion,0,0,0,,My Semblance has not been \Ncompletely exhausted yet, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.92,0:06:52.51,main,Ozpin,0,0,0,,By the way, what kind of power \Ndoes his Semblance have?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.70,0:06:56.42,main,Pyrrha,0,0,0,,Well, we don't know yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.42,0:06:59.46,main,Ren,0,0,0,,He has only just learned \Nhow to activate his Aura.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.46,0:07:03.53,main,Nora,0,0,0,,Seriously! I was so surprised that he \Nwas fighting without his Semblance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.65,0:07:07.69,main,Ozpin,0,0,0,,Sometimes battle helps to awaken powers...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.69,0:07:11.71,main,Ozpin,0,0,0,,powers hidden deep inside oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.69,0:07:31.13,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,Has Ruby fallen asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.63,0:07:39.53,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,Have Yang, Blake, and the \Nothers also fallen asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.49,0:07:49.95,italics,Weiss,0,0,0,,Mirror...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.93,0:07:57.08,italics,Weiss,0,0,0,,Tell me something,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.15,0:08:11.48,italics,Weiss,0,0,0,,Tell me who's the loneliest of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.19,0:08:25.26,italics,Weiss,0,0,0,,Mirror, what's inside of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.55,0:08:40.71,italics,Weiss,0,0,0,,Tell me, can a heart be turned to stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.86,0:08:49.97,italics,Weiss,0,0,0,,Mirror, mirror, what's behind you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.97,0:08:56.39,italics,Weiss,0,0,0,,Save me from the things I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.31,0:09:03.14,italics,Weiss,0,0,0,,I can keep it from the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.14,0:09:10.93,italics,Weiss,0,0,0,,Why won't you let me hide from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.40,0:09:17.72,italics,Weiss,0,0,0,,Mirror, mirror...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.07,0:09:24.86,italics,Weiss,0,0,0,,Tell me something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.96,0:09:39.26,italics,Weiss,0,0,0,,Who's the loneliest of all?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.06,0:09:58.29,italics,Weiss,0,0,0,,I'm the loneliest of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.31,0:10:23.54,main,Bashful Klein,0,0,0,,Aw, don't look around so much. \NIt's really embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.37,0:10:33.05,main,Yang,0,0,0,,I can't reach Ruby or Jaune.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.05,0:10:37.50,main,Yang,0,0,0,,It's like our shed back home, \Nexcept 100 times creepier.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.50,0:10:40.83,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Covered in junk that never gets cleaned up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.83,0:10:44.72,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Oh... I mean, I wasn't talking about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.72,0:10:46.60,main,Yang,0,0,0,,I'm talking about this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.60,0:10:48.25,main,Blake,0,0,0,,I feel the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.02,0:10:53.18,main,Blake,0,0,0,,I wonder if it is a gathering spot \Nfor things that have no other place to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.27,0:11:00.65,main,Blake,0,0,0,,The White Fang.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.53,0:11:20.33,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Yang.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.33,0:11:24.44,main,Yang,0,0,0,,A relic! This must be \Nthe relic meant for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.44,0:11:26.08,main,Yang,0,0,0,,I knew we'd find one!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.38,0:11:32.42,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.22,0:11:35.21,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.78,0:11:40.09,main,Yang,0,0,0,,What? What? What just appeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.81,0:11:46.73,main,Yang,0,0,0,,I can't tell if they're Grimm \Nor the White Fang.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.35,0:11:49.24,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Why are they so tame?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.24,0:11:50.96,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Probably because I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.96,0:11:54.95,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Maybe to Weiss, they and I are alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.95,0:11:57.55,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Hey, you don't know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.55,0:12:01.13,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Remember, the Grimm made this dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.13,0:12:02.63,main,Blake,0,0,0,,I think I understand why.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.63,0:12:03.49,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.49,0:12:08.58,main,Blake,0,0,0,,I used to believe that the Schnee Dust \NCompany and people persecuting Faunus
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.58,0:12:11.46,main,Blake,0,0,0,,were all dangerous and terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.46,0:12:12.77,main,Blake,0,0,0,,The same way she thinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.59,0:12:17.64,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Deep in my heart, \NI knew they weren't all that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.37,0:12:23.79,main,Blake,0,0,0,,But I convinced myself that their \Nhostility gave me a reason to fight them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.79,0:12:30.10,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Hmm... Well, even if you did, \Nyou aren't like that anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.10,0:12:32.22,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Anyway, let's take this and hurry back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.73,0:12:34.80,main,Yang,0,0,0,,And then get rid of the Grimm.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.80,0:12:36.27,main,Yang,0,0,0,,I'll use my coin, so—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.59,0:12:40.49,main,Blake,0,0,0,,If we do that, we'll just be \Nstopped by Negative Weiss again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.49,0:12:43.31,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Inside the dream, \Nwe're no match for her powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.31,0:12:45.54,main,Yang,0,0,0,,We don't know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.54,0:12:48.47,main,Yang,0,0,0,,I'm sure Ruby is doing her best right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.47,0:12:49.75,main,Yang,0,0,0,,We should hurry—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.75,0:12:51.13,main,Blake,0,0,0,,I'm sure she understands
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.64,0:12:56.42,main,Blake,0,0,0,,that if we don't think of a better plan, \Nwe have no chance of winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.42,0:13:00.37,main,Yang,0,0,0,,We've done enough thinking already. \NWhat else can we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.37,0:13:04.68,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Get a Grimm allergy like Jaune, \Nso we can sneak in like cowards?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.68,0:13:06.08,main,Yang,0,0,0,,That's not how I do things!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.08,0:13:08.87,main,Blake,0,0,0,,I'm telling you, brute force won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.87,0:13:12.06,main,Blake,0,0,0,,Oh... But there might be another way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.06,0:13:12.94,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.40,0:13:41.54,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,So there's a reason for this, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.24,0:14:05.27,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,The door we need isn't opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.27,0:14:07.53,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,We can only get into buildings close by.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.53,0:14:09.94,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,There aren't any robot soldiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.94,0:14:12.71,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,If we go now, we can probably \Nmake it to that building.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.71,0:14:14.75,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Are we really going there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.75,0:14:17.74,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,We really should look for \NYang and Blake instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.74,0:14:20.42,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,We've already used up \Nall of our coins, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.42,0:14:23.52,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Weiss will fall asleep \Nwhile we're doing that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.52,0:14:27.41,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,She'll never wake up again. \NWeiss—the real Weiss—said so.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.41,0:14:30.01,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,But what if the statue on \Nthe building starts moving again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.70,0:14:34.08,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,We don't know where more soldiers \Nor thorns will appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.50,0:14:38.67,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,We can't beat Negative Weiss. \NWe can't start acting recklessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.67,0:14:41.33,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Then I'll think of a plan \Nthat isn't reckless.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.23,0:14:52.96,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,This train... nothing blocked it \Nfrom coming here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.96,0:14:54.54,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.96,0:14:58.47,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,I wonder if we can ride the train \Nall the way to that building.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.47,0:14:59.54,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.54,0:15:01.47,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,There aren't any tracks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.47,0:15:03.91,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,There weren't tracks before, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.91,0:15:06.34,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,It should move as long as I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.34,0:15:08.99,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,You? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.99,0:15:13.40,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Weiss said that to me. \NThat I can move around freely.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.03,0:15:19.31,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Weiss didn't hate me, either. \NSo I'm sure she'll let us through.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.61,0:15:20.83,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,She'll understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.83,0:15:23.52,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,But that was Weiss, not Negative Weiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.52,0:15:25.88,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Negative Weiss is the one \Nthat'll come after us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.88,0:15:30.20,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,If she does, that means Weiss \Nhasn't fallen asleep yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.58,0:15:34.33,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,We could buy some time while we wait \Nfor Yang and the others to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.27,0:15:37.48,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Are we bringing these girls along, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.90,0:15:41.55,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I want to help Weiss become more free.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.57,0:15:46.67,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,It might sound selfish, but I think \Nit's the right thing to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.67,0:15:49.25,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,so I think these girls should fight, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.25,0:15:52.46,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Hey, now, did you forget what I told you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.98,0:15:58.02,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,The girls will turn into monsters \Nand go on a rampage again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.02,0:16:00.46,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,But that happened because of the Grimm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.46,0:16:05.26,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,The Pyrrha who stayed with you \Ndidn't turn into a monster, did she?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.26,0:16:06.51,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.51,0:16:12.00,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,And all I told them was \Nto fight for freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.00,0:16:14.37,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,That's probably why they went on a rampage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.37,0:16:17.14,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Then what will you make them do next?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.14,0:16:20.12,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I'll ask them to fight for Weiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.71,0:16:23.63,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I want to get Weiss out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.34,0:16:26.94,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I want Weiss to realize she wants to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.54,0:16:52.90,main,Weiss,0,0,0,,What is happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.50,0:17:04.01,main,Whitley,0,0,0,,What? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.29,0:17:47.53,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Phew...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.04,0:17:51.67,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Of course a Company train \Nwould be packed full of Dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.10,0:17:53.83,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,We've got all the ammo we need!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.69,0:18:06.99,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Please! Let us through, Weiss!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.42,0:18:10.87,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Keep going!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.14,0:18:59.15,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Weiss...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.21,0:19:03.16,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,Let us pass, Weiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.16,0:19:05.83,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,If you trust me, let us pass!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.37,0:19:08.51,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Don't be foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.51,0:19:12.63,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Even at this stage, you still don't \Nunderstand what is and isn't allowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.30,0:19:16.65,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,I will pass judgment on you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.40,0:19:19.09,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,and put you to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.20,0:19:40.07,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Shoot! Keep shooting!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.51,0:19:52.92,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,It's no good. At this rate, we're done for.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.26,0:20:01.27,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Move, damn it! Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.41,0:20:15.65,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.65,0:20:22.61,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.90,0:20:32.31,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,Be a good girl and go to sleep, Ruby.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.13,0:20:37.46,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,I have to save Weiss!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.48,0:20:55.28,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,This is the end for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.78,0:21:01.61,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.97,0:21:33.77,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.22,0:21:40.22,main,Jaune,0,0,0,,Yang!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.55,0:21:41.57,main,Yang,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.95,0:21:44.69,main,Negative Weiss,0,0,0,,The White Fang! But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.50,0:21:58.50,main,Negative Blake,0,0,0,,Daughter of the Schnee family!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.50,0:22:00.32,main,Negative Blake,0,0,0,,Humans or Faunus—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.32,0:22:04.18,main,Negative Blake,0,0,0,,I'll show you which is superior and just!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.87,0:23:38.54,main,Ruby,0,0,0,,"Mirror of Darkness."
